        <body>
            <div type="poem" rhyme="aabbccddeefgf">             
                <head type ="title"><hi rend="caps">F</hi><hi rend="smallcaps">arewell to</hi> <placeName corresp="#SCOTLAND"><hi rend="caps">S</hi><hi rend="smallcaps">cotland</hi></placeName></head>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>O what a change from pretty <placeName corresp="#PERTH">Perth</placeName> so near,</l>
                    <l>To dreary heather, and to streams so clear,&#x2014;</l>
                    <l>To rocks, and stones! Upon the dreary way</l>
                    <l>No sun is shining, as on sprightly May.</l>
                    <l>Again it changes to the winding <geogName corresp="#EARN">Earn</geogName>,&#x2014;</l>
                    <l>&#x02BC;Tis shallow water, but it has no fern;</l>
                    <l>But it is precious for its shining drops;</l>
                    <l>And sometimes from the <geogName corresp="#EARN">river</geogName> a fish pops.</l>
                    <l>Again it changes to a steep, steep hill,</l>
                    <l>And it is cold, do anything you will.</l>
                    <l>In short, such changes <placeName corresp="#SCOTLAND">Scotland</placeName> does now take,</l>
                    <l>That I can&#x02BC;t tell them, and<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="on_scotland_glosses_#COLLINGWOODSENDGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l><space quantity="28" unit="chars"/><hi rend="italic">an end I make</hi></l>
                </lg>
            </div>
